    {
      "name": "Products with Cloudinary Upload",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Product with File Upload (Cloudinary)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "name",
                  "value": "T-Shirt Premium",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Product name"
                },
                {
                  "key": "description",
                  "value": "Premium quality cotton t-shirt with Cloudinary images",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Product description"
                },
                {
                  "key": "isActive",
                  "value": "true",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Product active status"
                },
                {
                  "key": "images",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "Upload image files (max 5) - Select actual files when running in Postman GUI"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/products/upload",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "products",
                "upload"
              ]
            },
            "description": "📸 Create a new product with file upload to Cloudinary.\n\n**How to use:**\n1. In Postman GUI: Select file(s) for 'images' field\n2. Images will be uploaded to Cloudinary\n3. Auto-optimized and stored in CDN\n4. Returns Cloudinary URLs\n\n**Features:**\n- Upload up to 5 images\n- Automatic optimization\n- CDN delivery\n- Max 5MB per file\n- Formats: JPEG, PNG, WEBP, GIF"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 201\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Product created with Cloudinary images\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('id');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('name');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('images');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.images).to.be.an('array');",
                  "    ",
                  "    if (jsonData.images.length > 0) {",
                  "        pm.expect(jsonData.images[0]).to.have.property('url');",
                  "        pm.expect(jsonData.images[0]).to.have.property('publicId');",
                  "        pm.expect(jsonData.images[0].url).to.include('res.cloudinary.com');",
                  "        pm.environment.set('productIdCloudinary', jsonData.id);",
                  "    }",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload Image to Existing Product (Cloudinary)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "image",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "Single image file to upload"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}/images/upload",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "products",
                "{{productId}}",
                "images",
                "upload"
              ]
            },
            "description": "📸 Upload a single image to an existing product.\n\n**How to use:**\n1. Select a file for the 'image' field\n2. Image will be uploaded to Cloudinary\n3. Stored in product-specific folder\n4. Returns Cloudinary URL\n\n**Features:**\n- Single file upload\n- Automatic optimization\n- CDN delivery\n- Max 5MB\n- Formats: JPEG, PNG, WEBP, GIF"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 201\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Image uploaded to Cloudinary\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('id');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('url');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('publicId');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.url).to.include('res.cloudinary.com');",
                  "    pm.environment.set('uploadedImageId', jsonData.id);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "description": "📸 **Cloudinary Image Upload Endpoints**\n\nThese endpoints allow file upload directly to Cloudinary cloud storage.\n\n**Features:**\n- ✅ Cloud storage (Cloudinary)\n- ✅ Automatic optimization\n- ✅ CDN delivery\n- ✅ Image transformations\n- ✅ Max 5MB per file\n- ✅ Formats: JPEG, PNG, WEBP, GIF\n\n**Setup Required:**\n1. Sign up: https://cloudinary.com\n2. Add credentials to .env\n3. Restart server\n\n**Note:** File upload only works in Postman GUI, not CLI."
    },
